        "id": 4,
        "type": "list-with-images",
        "name": null,
        "title": "Benefits of Cloud Ecommerce",
        "intro": null,
        "style": "dark",
        "colStyle": "col-lg-6",
        "items": [
            {
                "image": {
                    "url": "https://vc4test.blob.core.windows.net/blogs/scalable.png"
                },
                "title": "Scalability on Demand ",
                "text": "<p>Traffic variability due to seasonal spikes creates a unique situation for suppliers and retailers. Required hardware needs to have capacity that conforms to the traffic peaks (ex. Black Friday, Cyber Monday, etc.) even though most of the year this capacity is not needed. The cloud offers an elastic solution, that allows for substantial variations in workload and meets the needs for seasonal or hourly promotional spikes in traffic. Cloud ecommerce solution resources can be scaled up and down to support your actual needs.</p>\n"
            },
            {
                "image": {
                    "url": "https://vc4test.blob.core.windows.net/blogs/secure.png"
                },
                "title": "Security",
                "text": "<p>Save time on risk assessment and data defense, so that you can focus on your business! When hosting your business in the cloud, you don&#39;t need to worry about maintaining and monitoring your servers. Security and protection of your network, physical facilities, applications, including data encryption and customers&#39;<br />\npersonal data safety can be excluded from the list of your concerns. Cloud hosting providers complete third-party certifications, and proper security is a priority for them. Additionally, the constant accessibility of your website and regular data backups ensure that your online presence will be available without any data loss in case of an emergency.</p>\n"
            },
            {
                "image": {
                    "url": "https://vc4test.blob.core.windows.net/blogs/payment.png"
                },
                "title": "Cost Effective Performance ",
                "text": "<p>The cloud is a perfect place for an ecommerce solution because you can pay for resources only when you need them. A cloud solution may save a company over 70% of the costs associated with building static environments scaled for traffic peaks - the hardware that may only be in use a few days a year. With cloud, you only pay for what you use.</p>\n"
            },
            {
                "image": {
                    "url": "https://vc4test.blob.core.windows.net/blogs/saas.png"
                },
                "title": "Easy accessibility from any place ",
                "text": "<p>If your business operates in multiple countries, a cloud-based solution offers clear advantages considering the speed required to roll out and manage an ecommerce application. With a digital commerce cloud you have a remote network of servers that responds dynamically to your demands to deliver content fast no matter where your customer is.</p>\n"
            }
