        "type": "list-with-images",
        "name": null,
        "title": "How Should I Evaluate Digital Commerce Vendors?",
        "intro": "<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">Cloud computing services fall under several distinct categories. Each of these models or their combinations allows you to create the perfect foundation for your ecommerce suite.</h3>\n",
        "style": "light",
        "colStyle": "col-lg-6",
        "items": [
            {
                "image": {
                    "url": null
                },
                "title": "IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service)",
                "text": "<p>This type of cloud service focuses on providing on-demand data storage on disks and virtual servers. Customers purchase a remote datacenter infrastructure service instead of having to purchase their own hardware. Examples include cloud services offered by established well-known brands, such as Amazon and Microsoft.</p>\n"
            },
            {
                "image": {
                    "url": null
                },
                "title": "PaaS (Platform as a Service)",
                "text": "<p>A cloud development platform that allows its users to develop, manage, and launch applications within a self-service portal with a ready-to-use cloud computing infrastructure. Most platforms provide the basics so that you don&#39;t have to start from scratch. The operating system is supported and frequently upgraded, and the services for your ecommerce solution can be built using certain modules.</p>\n\n<p>Examples of Platform-as-a-Service are Google App Engine, Cloudfy, and Cloudsuite.</p>\n"
            },
            {
                "image": {
                    "url": null
                },
                "title": "SaaS (Software as a Service)",
                "text": "<p>Software-as-a-Service means that a third-party hosting service provider gives clients access to various cloud ecommerce solutions on a pay-as-you-go basis.</p>\n\n<p>This service type is very popular among ecommerce vendors, and applications allow your business to improve customer experience and expand your store with advanced features, such as smart shopping carts or mobile-friendly applications. Among the most popular SaaS solutions are Salesforce, NetSuite, Slack and others.</p>\n\n<p>An optimal choice for an e-commerce business however would be a solution that combines a platform with a ready-to-use set of software tools. In other words, PaaS and SaaS built specifically for digital commerce. Our cloud-based ecommerce technology - Virto Commerce, is considered one of the best e-commerce platforms available for B2B and enterprise customers, please click to learn more about Virto Commerce for B2B, B2C and Startups.</p>\n"
            }
